result.execSummary:
The defendant Quade Lakwhan Workman was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Felon Possess Firearm [Modifiers: Repeater], a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.29(2)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes:
Restitution set at zero.
Court costs and victim/witness surcharges are to be collected by DOC from up to 25% of prison funds, balance to be paid by 1/14/2018; nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment.

No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause.

Mental health assessment and any recommended treatment to include any counseling, therapy and taking any prescribed medications.
Successfully complete a Cognitive thinking Behavioral Modification program.

Defendant Quade Lakwhan Workman in court with attorney Donald Crawford Dudley.  Nathaniel Emery Adamson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Additional statements by:  Sentencing Proceeded. Statements by the State, defense counsel and defendant.   The Court sentenced defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT in the Wisconsin State Prisons for 3 YEARS.  INITIAL CONFINEMENT of 1 YEARS and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 2 YEARS, consecutive to any other sentence, credit for 183 days.
Defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and is not eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.
-Restitution set at zero
-Court costs and victim/witness surcharges are to be collected by DOC from up to 25% of prison funds, balance to be paid by 01/14/2018; nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment.
-Defendant is to provide a DNA sample and pay the related surcharge  to be collected by DOC from up to 25% of prison funds, balance to be paid by -1/14/2018; nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment.
CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
-No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause;
-Mental health assessment and any recommended treatment to include any couseling, therapy and taking any prescribed medications
-Employment or school
-Successfully complete a Cognitive Thinking Behavioral Modification Program
-Complete 20 hours of community service
Court advised the defendant that as a convicted felon he may no longer use or possess any firearms or body armor; also he may not vote in any election until his/her civil rights have been restored.

Defendant Quade Lakwhan Workman in court with attorney Donald Crawford Dudley.  Defendant Quade Lakwhan Workman in custody.  Nathaniel Emery Adamson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Pursuant to plea negotations, and on motion of the State, Court ordered the the repeater enhancer dismissed. Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.
